      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`log`}</inlineCode></a>{` events, allowing you to enrich
events with geolocation data from the MaxMind GeoIP2 and GeoLite2 city
databases.`}</p>
    {
      /*
          THIS FILE IS AUTOGENERATED!
           To make changes please edit the template located at:
           website/docs/reference/transforms/geoip.md.erb
      */
    }
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "configuration"
    }}>{`Configuration`}</h2>
    <Tabs block={true} defaultValue="common" values={[{
      "label": "Common",
      "value": "common"
    }, {
      "label": "Advanced",
      "value": "advanced"
    }]} mdxType="Tabs">
      <TabItem value="common" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-toml",
            "metastring": "title=\"vector.toml\"",
            "title": "\"vector.toml\""
          }}>{`[transforms.my_transform_id]
  type = "geoip" # required
  inputs = ["my-source-or-transform-id"] # required
  database = "/path/to/GeoLite2-City.mmdb" # required
  source = "ip_address" # required
  target = "geoip" # optional, default
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="advanced" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-toml",
            "metastring": "title=\"vector.toml\"",
            "title": "\"vector.toml\""
          }}>{`[transforms.my_transform_id]
  type = "geoip" # required
  inputs = ["my-source-or-transform-id"] # required
  database = "/path/to/GeoLite2-City.mmdb" # required
  source = "ip_address" # required
  target = "geoip" # optional, default
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
    </Tabs>
    <Fields filters={true} mdxType="Fields">
      <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["/path/to/GeoLite2-City.mmdb"]} groups={[]} name={"database"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={true} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "database"
        }}>{`database`}</h3>
        <p>{`Path to the MaxMind GeoIP2 or GeoLite2 binary city database file
(`}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`GeoLite2-City.mmdb`}</inlineCode>{`). Other databases, such as the the country database are
not supported.`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["ip_address", "x-forwarded-for", "parent.child", "array[0]"]} groups={[]} name={"source"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={true} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "source"
        }}>{`source`}</h3>
        <p>{`The field name that contains the IP address. This field should contain a valid
IPv4 or IPv6 address.
See `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "#field-notation-syntax"
          }}>{`Field Notation Syntax`}</a>{` for more info.`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={true} defaultValue={"geoip"} enumValues={null} examples={["geoip", "parent.child"]} groups={[]} name={"target"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "target"
        }}>{`target`}</h3>
        <p>{`The default field to insert the resulting GeoIP data into. See
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "#output"
          }}>{`output`}</a>{` for more info.
See `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "#field-notation-syntax"
          }}>{`Field Notation Syntax`}</a>{` for more info.`}</p>
      </Field>
    </Fields>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "fields"
    }}>{`Fields`}</h2>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-javascript",
        "metastring": "title=\"example log event\"",
        "title": "\"example",
        "log": true,
        "event\"": true
      }}>{`{
  // ...
  "geoip": {
    "city_name": "New York",
    "continent_code": "AF",
    "country_code": "US",
    "latitude": "51.75",
    "longitude": "-1.25",
    "postal_code": "07094",
    "timezone": "America/New_York"
  }
  // ...
}
`}</code></pre>
    <Fields filters={true} mdxType="Fields">
      <Field common={false} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={[]} groups={[]} name={"geoip"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"struct"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "geoip"
        }}>{`geoip`}</h3>
        <p>{`The root field containing all geolocation data as sub-fields.
See `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "#complex-processing"
          }}>{`Complex Processing`}</a>{` for more info.`}</p>
        <Fields filters={false} mdxType="Fields">
          <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["New York", "Brooklyn", "Chicago"]} groups={[]} name={"city_name"} path={"geoip"} relevantWhen={null} required={true} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
            <h4 {...{
              "id": "city_name"
            }}>{`city_name`}</h4>
            <p>{`The city name associated with the IP address.`}</p>
          </Field>
          <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={{
            "AF": "Africa",
            "AN": "Antarctica",
            "AS": "Asia",
            "EU": "Europe",
            "NA": "North America",
            "OC": "Oceania",
            "SA": "South America"
          }} examples={["AF", "AN", "AS", "EU", "NA", "OC", "SA"]} groups={[]} name={"continent_code"} path={"geoip"} relevantWhen={null} required={true} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
            <h4 {...{
              "id": "continent_code"
            }}>{`continent_code`}</h4>
            <p>{`The continent code associated with the IP address.`}</p>
          </Field>
          <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["US", "US-PR", "FR", "FR-BL", "GB", "A1", "A2"]} groups={[]} name={"country_code"} path={"geoip"} relevantWhen={null} required={true} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
            <h4 {...{
              "id": "country_code"
            }}>{`country_code`}</h4>
            <p>{`The `}<a parentName="p" {...{
                "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-2"
              }}>{`ISO 3166-2 country codes`}</a>{` associated with the IP address.`}</p>
          </Field>
          <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["51.75"]} groups={[]} name={"latitude"} path={"geoip"} relevantWhen={null} required={true} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
            <h4 {...{
              "id": "latitude"
            }}>{`latitude`}</h4>
            <p>{`The latitude associated with the IP address.`}</p>
          </Field>
          <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["-1.25"]} groups={[]} name={"longitude"} path={"geoip"} relevantWhen={null} required={true} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
            <h4 {...{
              "id": "longitude"
            }}>{`longitude`}</h4>
            <p>{`The longitude associated with the IP address.`}</p>
          </Field>
          <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["07094", "10010", "OX1"]} groups={[]} name={"postal_code"} path={"geoip"} relevantWhen={null} required={true} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
            <h4 {...{
              "id": "postal_code"
            }}>{`postal_code`}</h4>
            <p>{`The postal code associated with the IP address.`}</p>
          </Field>
          <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["America/New_York", "Asia/Atyrau", "Europe/London"]} groups={[]} name={"timezone"} path={"geoip"} relevantWhen={null} required={true} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
            <h4 {...{
              "id": "timezone"
            }}>{`timezone`}</h4>
            <p>{`The timezone associated with the IP address in `}<a parentName="p" {...{
                "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tz_database#Names_of_time_zones"
              }}>{`IANA time zone
format`}</a>{`. A full list of time zones can be found
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
                "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_tz_database_time_zones"
              }}>{`here`}</a>{`.`}</p>
          </Field>
        </Fields>
      </Field>
    </Fields>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "how-it-works"
    }}>{`How It Works`}</h2>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "complex-processing"
    }}>{`Complex Processing`}</h3>
    <p>{`If you encounter limitations with the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "#geoip"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`geoip`}</inlineCode></a>{`
transform then we recommend using a `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://vector.dev/components/?functions%5B%5D=program"
      }}>{`runtime transform`}</a>{`.
These transforms are designed for complex processing and give you the power of
full programming runtime.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "environment-variables"
    }}>{`Environment Variables`}</h3>
    <p>{`Environment variables are supported through all of Vector's configuration.
Simply add `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`\${MY_ENV_VAR}`}</inlineCode>{` in your Vector configuration file and the variable
will be replaced before being evaluated.`}</p>
    <p>{`You can learn more in the
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/setup/configuration/#environment-variables"
      }}>{`Environment Variables`}</a>{` section.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "field-notation-syntax"
    }}>{`Field Notation Syntax`}</h3>
    <p>{`The `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "#source"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`source`}</inlineCode></a>{` and `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "#target"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`target`}</inlineCode></a>{` options
support `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/reference/field-path-notation/"
      }}>{`Vector's field notation syntax`}</a>{`,
enabling access to root-level, nested, and array field values. For example:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-toml",
        "metastring": "title=\"vector.toml\"",
        "title": "\"vector.toml\""
      }}>{`[transforms.my_geoip_transform_id]
  # ...
  source = "ip_address"
  source = "x-forwarded-for"
  source = "parent.child"
  source = "array[0]"
  # ...
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`You can learn more about Vector's field notation in the
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/reference/field-path-notation/"
      }}>{`field notation reference`}</a>{`.`}</p>
    </MDXLayout>;
}

